This paper deals with the problem of dense 3D shape acquisition of swimming humans or live fish in underwater environments. The proposed solution involves using a stereo camera pair with a pattern projector and a convolutional neural network to remove the effects of bubbles and water fluctuation. This work involves computer vision (stereo reconstruction), robotics (underwater environment), graphics (3D shape acquisition), and multimedia (image processing). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.RO (Robotics), cs.GR (Graphics), cs.GT (Computer Graphics), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
